locations.name: PreFlight O'Hare - Premium Covered Self Park

address.full_address: 4155 North Mannheim Road, Schiller Park, IL 60176

provider_data.navigation_tip: Enter this location at the intersection of N Mannheim Rd and United Pkwy. This is the PreFlight O'Hare garage. From the intersection of W Irving Park Rd. and N Mannheim Rd., head south on N Mannheim Rd. towards United Pkwy. Turn left on United Pkwy., and the entrance will be directly ahead. The entrance will be past the red PreFlight Airport Parking sign, and just north of the BP gas station and Dunkin Donuts.
restrictions: 24/7 shuttle service is available at no cost from this location. Shuttles depart from the center lobby every 4-8 minutes and drop customers off at all terminals.

PreFlight Facts:We never close. We are 2.5 miles or 7–12 minutes from the airport and our shuttles run every 4–8 minutes. We recommend that you arrive at our facility at least 30 minutes prior to the time that you want to be at the airport.
Wheelchair Accessible Shuttles: Please call at least 24 hours before you arrive at our facility so that we can have a wheel chair accessible vehicle ready to take you to the airport.
Height restriction: 9' 10"

If you return to O'Hare International Airport between midnight and 8:00 a.m., please call (847) 678-9234 for pick up. At all other times, a bus will arrive every 4 - 8 minutes at the airport's bus and shuttle center.

Please be mindful of your scheduled arrival and exit times. If you arrive early, or stay later than your SpotHero reservation time period, you will have to pay the overage to the onsite cashier before you can exit.

PreFlight ORD is a four story parking garage that offers three different parking options:

Roof top parking – located on the fourth level; this is the most economical option

Economy Covered – located on floors 2 & 3; this area is covered and the stalls are wider than rooftop parking

Premium Covered – located on the ground floor; this area is covered and offers the widest parking spaces at O’Hare.
THE AVERAGE SHUTTLE TIME TO THE TERMINALS IS 8–12 MINUTES.
This rate is only valid for premium covered parking on the ground floor of the parking garage.

departure.text:
Return: NEW PICKUP LOCATION! Airport pickup location for terminals 1, 2 & 3 is now at terminal 2, lower level, middle lane, outside door 2C.

From terminal 1 with no checked luggage: stay inside security and follow the signs to terminal 2. Go to terminal 2 baggage claim area and exit door 2C (near information desk), go out to the middle curb and look to the right for the PreFlight bus.

From terminal 1 baggage claim: exit door 1F (near baggage claim 1), go to the right to the terminal 2 middle curb. During cold weather, you can walk inside terminal 2 to door 2C near the information desk or follow the signs using the lower tunnel to terminal 2, then up to baggage claim, then to door 2C near the information desk. Go out to the middle lane and look right for the bus.

From terminal 2: go to baggage claim and exit door 2C near the information desk, go out to the middle curb and look right for the PreFlight bus.

From terminal 3: go to baggage claim and exit door 3A (farthest left), go left to the terminal 2 middle curb.

For Terminal 5 pickup: please call or text for pickup once you clear customs. Proceed to the lower level outer curb outside door 5E for pick up.

Phone: 847.678.9234, Text: 224.330.9402

The shuttle bus will return you to the ground floor lobby.

locations.name: Park & Ride Lot - Uncovered Self Park

provider_data.navigation_tip: Enter this location at 8501 W Higgins Rd. This is the Park & Ride lot. It is located on the south side of W Higgins Rd. between S Cumberland Ave. and N East River Rd. The entrance is marked by a white '8501' sign with silver lettering. After turning off Higgins Rd., please make sure to stay right at the entry, entering the main parking lot after scanning your bar code at the kiosk entry. Drive straight through the main parking lot to the back parking area (bordering the Kennedy Expressway.) Do not park in the visitor parking lot to the main building designated parking. Please only use the blue spots in the south portion of the lot.
restrictions: Due to liability issues, The Marriott is not able to transport guests to-and-from O'hare that are not either staying at the Marriott or parking directly through the Marriott's Spot Hero parking reservations.

During high-demand periods, the SpotHero spaces outlined in blue may be occupied. ONLY in those cases, customers are permitted to park just north of designated SpotHero spots. This is the direction AWAY from the Blue Line stop. There should always be a stall available.
SpotHero and local parking provider are not responsible for theft, damage to your vehicle, or personal property. Please keep vehicle locked and do not leave valuables in your car.

This facility does NOT provide a shuttle. The Blue Line train station is on the same property as this parking garage. The Blue Line runs 24/7 with elevator access. Access to the Cumberland Blue Line station walkway can be found at the south end of the lot, next to the Kennedy Expressway.

To access O'Hare International Airport, take the Blue Line two stops north towards O'Hare. More information on the train station and schedule is available here: http://www.transitchicago.com/travel_information/station.aspx?StopId=48.
